      Department of Computer Science, Faculty of Mathematics and
      Natural Sciences, Universitas Lampung
repository-code: 'https://github.com/dafahan/cell-lookup-bench'
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.21440722
identifiers:
  - type: doi
    value: 10.5281/zenodo.21440722
    description: Concept DOI, always resolves to the latest release
  - type: doi
    value: 10.5281/zenodo.21440723
    description: DOI of release v1.0.0
abstract: >-
  A retrieval-free benchmark that isolates the reading-side failure
  of language models on table cell lookup. Each question is paired
  with a gold context guaranteed to contain the answer, rendered in
  seven information-equivalent representations, and scored by
  deterministic exact match without an LLM judge. Includes a 2x2
  controlled experiment that separates column-label misalignment
  from value repetition as candidate causes, five synthetic stress
  structures, and raw responses from ten checkpoints across five
  open-weight model families.
keywords:
  - table question answering
  - large language models
  - benchmark
  - column indexing
  - table verbalization
  - reproducibility
